Both deliverables are written to the working directory.

**`transcript.json`** — 25 iterations covering univariate screening, multivariable regression, identification of feature_008 as the only treatment-like variable, and a systematic interaction/subgroup search. Validated against `transcript_schema.json`.

**`analysis_summary.txt`** — narrative summary of the supported and refuted hypotheses.

Key finding: `feature_008` is a treatment whose effect on `objective_response` is concentrated in the subgroup `feature_013=0 AND feature_015=0 AND feature_021=0 AND feature_027=0` (N=15,681): response rises from 17% to 80% (OR 19, +0.626 absolute). Outside that subgroup the treatment effect is essentially zero (+0.007). The continuous biomarker `feature_022` is closely tied to `feature_013` and shows the same monotone effect-modification pattern. None of the other "no-main-effect" binary features (005/006/011/017/019/023/004) showed treatment-by-feature heterogeneity surviving Bonferroni adjustment.
